1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,962
(Luke 10:38): I quote first in Latin this text from the gospel.

2
00:00:05,912 --> 00:00:13,887
The translation reads: ‘Our Lord Jesus Christ went up into a certain fastness and was received by a certain virgin who was a wife.

3
00:00:13,887 --> 00:00:15,237
Mark the term.

4
00:00:15,237 --> 00:00:18,887
Needs must it be a virgin by whom Jesus is received.

5
00:00:18,887 --> 00:00:25,387
Virgin is, in other words, a person void of alien images, free as he was when he existed not.

6
00:00:25,387 --> 00:00:37,887
It may be questioned: Man born and launched on rational life, how can he be as free from images as he was when he was not, he knowing a variety of things, images all of them: how can he possibly be void thereof?

7
00:00:37,887 --> 00:01:02,562
I answer that, were I sufficiently intelligent to have within me intellectually the sum of all the forms conceived by man and which subsist in God himself, I having no property in them and no idea of ownership, positive or negative, past or to come, but standing in the present now perfectly free in the will of God and doing it perpetually: then verily I were a virgin, unhandicapped by forms, just as I was when I was not.

8
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:15,350
Further, I hold that the fact of being virgin does not deprive a man at all of works that he has done: he is untrammelled, virgin-free of them in the sovran truth, even as Jesus is absolutely free and virgin in himself.

9
00:01:15,350 --> 00:01:24,625
According to the masters, likeness, likeness only, is the cause of union, so man must be maiden, virgin, to receive the virgin Jesus.

10
00:01:24,625 --> 00:01:29,025
Now lay this fact to heart: the ever virgin is never fruitful.

11
00:01:29,025 --> 00:01:31,812
To be fruitful the soul must be wife.

12
00:01:31,812 --> 00:01:36,212
Spouse is the noblest title of the soul, nobler than virgin.

13
00:01:36,212 --> 00:01:40,925
For a man to receive God within him is good and in receiving he is virgin.

14
00:01:40,925 --> 00:01:52,100
But for God to be fruitful in him is still better: the fruits of his gift being gratitude therefor, and in this newborn thankfulness the spirit is the spouse bearing Jesus back into his Father’s heart.

15
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:59,362
Many good gifts received in maidenhood are not brought forth in wifely fruitfulness, reborn in praise and thanks to God.

16
00:01:59,362 --> 00:02:04,487
Such gifts corrupt and come to naught, man being no better and no happier for them.

17
00:02:04,487 --> 00:02:11,212
In this case his virginity is useless because to his virginity he does not add the perfect fruitfulness of wife.

18
00:02:11,212 --> 00:02:12,837
That is the mischief.

19
00:02:12,837 --> 00:02:19,425
Hence my text, ‘Jesus ascended to a certain fastness and was received by a certain maid who was a wife.

20
00:02:19,425 --> 00:02:22,050
It must be so, as I have said.

21
00:02:22,050 --> 00:02:25,437
Wedded folks yield little more than one fruit yearly.

22
00:02:25,437 --> 00:02:35,362
But it is other wedded ones that I have now in mind: those whose hearts are wedded to praying, fasting, vigils or other outward discipline and mortifications of the flesh.

23
00:02:35,362 --> 00:03:02,075
A predilection for this sort of thing, involving loss of freedom to wait instantly on God in the here and now, and follow him alone in the light wherein he would fain show thee what to do and what to leave undone, moment by moment, fresh and clearly, as though thou hadst naught else, nor would nor could not: any such proclivity or preoccupation which constantly deprives thee of this freedom I call here a year, and thy soul yields no fruit till she is done with this work of thy affection nor

24
00:03:02,075 --> 00:03:09,362
hast thou any trust in God or in thyself till thou hast finished with thy predilection; in other words, thou hast no peace.

25
00:03:09,362 --> 00:03:12,287
There is no fruit till thy own work is done.

26
00:03:12,287 --> 00:03:17,862
I reckon this a year and one whose yield is poor; the proceeds of affection not of freedom.

27
00:03:17,862 --> 00:03:21,625
And these folks I call wedded, yoked to their affections.

28
00:03:21,625 --> 00:03:26,387
Their crop is small and undersized at that, so I say, in God’s sight.

29
00:03:26,548 --> 00:03:32,210
The virgin wife, free and unbound in her affections is ever as near God as to herself.

30
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:37,298
She abounds in fruit and big withal, no more nor less than God is himself.

31
00:03:37,298 --> 00:03:54,173
This fruit, his birth, does that virgin bear who is a wife: daily she yields her hundred and her thousandfold, nay, numberless her labours and her fruits in that most noble ground, the very ground, to speak more plainly, wherein the Father is begetting his eternal Word: there she is big with fruit.

32
00:03:54,173 --> 00:04:09,510
For Jesus, light and shine of the paternal heart (according to St Paul he is the ‘light and splendour’ of the Father’s heart), this Jesus is atoned with her and she with him, she is radiant with him and shining as the one alone, as one pure brilliant light in the paternal heart.

33
00:04:09,510 --> 00:04:18,898
Elsewhere I have declared, there is a power in the soul untouched by time and flesh, flowing from the Spirit, remaining in the Spirit, altogether spiritual.

34
00:04:18,898 --> 00:04:25,085
In this power is God, ever verdant, flowering in all the joy and glory of his actual self.

35
00:04:25,085 --> 00:04:41,660
Such dear delight, such inconceivable deep joy as none can fully tell, for in this power the eternal Father is procreating his eternal Son without a pause, the power being big with child, the Father’s Son and its own self this selfsame Son withal, in the unique power of the Father.

36
00:04:41,660 --> 00:05:03,348
Suppose a man absolute monarch, the sole possessor of all earthly goods; suppose he gave up all for God and was the poorest of the poor; and that God laid on him to boot a burden big as ever he did lay on mortal man, all which he bare down to his death and then God granted him one fleeting vision of his being in this power: so vehement would be his joy that poverty and suffering would be wiped out.

37
00:05:03,348 --> 00:05:12,435
Aye, though God gave him never any taste of heaven but this, yet would he have the guerdon of his passion, for God himself is in this power as in the eternal now.

38
00:05:12,435 --> 00:05:25,073
If a man’s spirit were always joined to God in this same power, he could not age For the now wherein God made the first man and the now wherein the last man disappears and the now I speak in, all are the same in God where there is but the now.

39
00:05:25,073 --> 00:05:31,785
Behold this man in the same light as God having in him no past nor yet to come, only one level of eternity.

40
00:05:31,785 --> 00:05:36,923
This man in truth has motion taken from him and all things stand intrinsic in him.

41
00:05:36,923 --> 00:05:44,535
Nothing new comes to him from future things nor yet by accident for he dwells in the now, ever new and unceasingly renewed.

42
00:05:44,535 --> 00:05:47,485
So dominant is God in this same power.

43
00:05:47,485 --> 00:05:54,673
There is another power, immortal too: proceeding from the Spirit, remaining in the Spirit, altogether spiritual.

44
00:05:54,673 --> 00:06:01,023
In this power God is fiery, aglow with all his riches, with all his sweetness and with all his bliss.

45
00:06:01,023 --> 00:06:08,560
Aye, in this power is such poignant joy, such vehement, immoderate delight as none can tell nor yet in truth reveal.

46
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:23,535
I say, moreover, if once a man in intellectual vision did really glimpse the bliss and joy therein, then all his sufferings, all God intends that he should suffer, would be a trifle, a mere nothing to him; nay, I say more, it would be pure joy and pleasure.

47
00:06:23,535 --> 00:06:27,985
Wouldst thou know for certain whether thy sufferings are thine own or God’s?

48
00:06:27,985 --> 00:06:29,860
Tell by these tokens.

49
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:35,310
Suffering for thyself, in whatever way, the suffering hurts thee and is hard to bear.

50
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:41,823
But suffering for God and God alone thy suffering hurts thee not nor does it burden thee, for God bears the load.

51
00:06:41,823 --> 00:06:54,448
Believe me, if there were a man willing to suffer on account of God and of God alone, then though he fell a sudden prey to the collective sufferings of all the world it would not trouble him nor bow him down, for God would be the bearer of his burden.

52
00:06:54,448 --> 00:07:02,860
If the burden they put upon my neck is forthwith shouldered by another I would as lief a hundred pounds as one, for not to me is it heavy and distressful.

53
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:08,210
In brief: man’s sufferings for God and God alone he makes both light and pleasant.

54
00:07:08,380 --> 00:07:15,305
I prefaced this sermon with the words: ‘Jesus went up into a fastness and was received by a virgin who was wife.

55
00:07:15,255 --> 00:07:16,142
Why?

56
00:07:16,142 --> 00:07:18,955
She must needs be virgin and wife too.

57
00:07:18,955 --> 00:07:21,905
How Jesus was received I have explained.

58
00:07:21,905 --> 00:07:26,467
I have not told the meaning of this fastness and that I will now proceed to do.

59
00:07:26,467 --> 00:07:31,067
From time to time I tell of the one power in the soul which alone is free.

60
00:07:31,067 --> 00:07:38,067
Sometimes I have called it the tabernacle of the soul; sometimes a spiritual light, anon I say it is a spark.

61
00:07:38,067 --> 00:07:41,355
But now I say: it is neither this nor that.

62
00:07:41,355 --> 00:07:46,880
Yet it is somewhat: somewhat more exalted over this and that than the heavens are above the earth.

63
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:52,780
So now I name it in a nobler fashion than before as regarding rank and mode which it transcends.

64
00:07:52,780 --> 00:07:58,405
It is of all names free, of all forms void: exempt and free as God is in himself.

65
00:07:58,405 --> 00:08:03,942
It is one and simple as God is one and simple, and no man can in any wise behold it.

66
00:08:03,942 --> 00:08:25,442
This same power I am speaking of, herein God blooms and thrives in all his Godhood and the spirit in God; in this very power the Father bears his only Son no less than in himself, for verily he liveth in this power, the spirit with the Father giving birth therein to his very Son, itself this selfsame Son, for in this light which is the light of truth, it is the Son himself.

67
00:08:25,442 --> 00:08:31,617
Could ye see with my heart ye would understand my words, but it is true, for truth itself has said it.

68
00:08:31,617 --> 00:08:56,792
So one and simple is this fastness, frowning above all ways, of which I mind me and am telling you, within the soul, that this high faculty I speak of is not worthy even of a fleeting glance therein; nor is that other power God glows and burns in, it durst not peer in either; so one and indivisible this refuge is, so way- and power-transcending this solitary one that never mode nor faculty has any insight there, not even God himself.

69
00:08:56,792 --> 00:09:05,080
Never for an instant, as God lives, does God see into this, nor did he ever look in his conditioned nature, in his guise of Person.

70
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:09,417
Note well, this one alone is lacking in every mode and quality.

71
00:09:09,417 --> 00:09:28,030
It follows that for God to see therein would cost him all his divine names and personal properties: all these he must forgo to look therein: only as one and indivisible, having no jot of mode or quality, not Father nor Son nor Holy Ghost as such, can he do this; as somewhat, yes, but not as this or that.

72
00:09:28,030 --> 00:09:37,942
As one and impartible behold him entering this one that here I call the fastness of the soul, but in no different guise can he get in: thus only does he enter and subsist in it.

73
00:09:37,942 --> 00:09:45,705
In part the soul is the same as God but not altogether.—This that I tell you is true: truth is my witness and my soul the pledge.

74
00:09:45,705 --> 00:09:52,392
May we be as this fastness whereinto on ascending Jesus is received to abide eternally as I have said.

75
00:09:52,392 --> 00:09:54,055
So help us God.

76
00:09:54,055 --> 00:09:55,005
Amen.
